 FOOTBALL fans are calling for a minute's applause for hit-and-run soldier Shaun Cole at Hearts' upcoming games. 
A social media campaign calling for the 22-year-old, from Edinburgh, to be honoured by the crowd in the 22nd minute of his team's matches was spreading on Facebook and Twitter last night.
 Pte Cole was found dead in a Miami street on Sunday after travelling to the US with two pals for the Ultra Music Festival. 
Police believe he was hit by a car which fled the scene.

